On Monday, July 18, 2005, at 02:54PM, Jack Dinan <jdinan(-at-)cox.net> wrote:

>What I see when I look through the orifice is a moveable metal vane 
>with a notch in it. This vane/notch is already a good way into the 
>circular opening. I estimate that perhaps 15 % of the area of the 
>opening is not obscured by the vane when it is cold. So very little 
>air is allowed through and this could lead to my low idle situation.

That's how the AAR works.

Unless you've got a vacuum leak from the two hoses and elbow that connect it to the manifold, because it bypasses the throttle it's responsible for raising the idle not lowering it because it's not closed.

What kind of lifters do you have, solid or hydraulic?

